> <OLD>
>
> Oh, the electronics of which made up all Cybertronians then still worked,
> but only as they would for the beastial equivalents.  But, the Widow could
> work with this for now.  Clicking her mandibles together then as she scanned
> the area further.

<NEW>

Oh yes, the spider lady had the right of it now. Enhanced senses
worked just fine in beast modes, but the cybertronian 'sensors' did
not seem to operate as they should. There was a growing level of
interference as the approached the cave that was before them. It had
been getting progressively worse as they came, but here, at the
entrance, and presumably if they went in, it would spike as it became
more pronounced.

> <OLD>
>
> Glancing to CRYOTEK, DINOBOT spoke along, "Underground, we located what
> seemed to be in essence a horizon of whatever is blocking.  Not a source,
> but a barrier beyond which it's approach scans went no further."
> Elaborating further, "And given that existence does not merely end at it's
> meeting, it seemed like there was a cavern of sorts along the bottom where
> sensor scans could not penetrate, and I felt it best to notify you."

SKYSHADOW nodded, as he stroked his chin, "We must be getting close to
the source of whatever this place is." He said thoughtfully.

"I concur." CRYOTEK said as he looked at DINOBOT.

"Great!" BANTOR said, "Now if you could just show this barrier we can
get on our way."

LEO PRIME grunted, "Easy Bantor." He said laying a calming hand on the
FUZOR." He looked at CRYOTEK, "I can feel the power of whatever this
thing getting stronger even as we stand here." He looked back a the
cave, "I don't think we have much more time."

CRYOTEK nodded, "Show us what you have DINOBOT."

(TAG)

- Preston
